item.description:
Input: A sequence of n numbers {a1, a2, a3, &hellip; an}
  Output: a permutation of {a1, a2, a3, &hellip; an} such that a1&rsquo; &lt; a2&rsquo; &lt; an&rsquo;
 How it works Basically the way most people sort a hand of playing cards. We start with an empty left hand and the the card face down. We remove one card at a time and insert it into the correct position of the hand.
